# TypeScript Standards

## Strict Typing

- Never use `any` - use `unknown` and narrow with type guards
- Export all public interfaces and types from `src/core/types.ts`
- Use generic type parameters for data payloads: `PendingAction<T>`
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections

## Error Handling

```typescript
// Use Result pattern for operations that can fail
type Result<T, E = Error> = { ok: true; value: T } | { ok: false; error: E };
```

- Wrap adapter errors in domain-specific error classes
- Never swallow errors silently - log or propagate
- Async functions must handle rejection paths

## Naming Conventions

- Interfaces: prefix with `I` for adapter contracts (`IStorageAdapter`)
- Types: PascalCase, no prefix (`PendingAction`, `SyncStatus`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (`MAX_RETRIES`, `DEFAULT_SYNC_INTERVAL`)
- Files: kebab-case (`sync-manager.ts`, `pending-queue.ts`)

## Exports

- Use named exports exclusively - no default exports
- Barrel files (`index.ts`) re-export the public API surface only
